Description: Text-to-speech plugin for Zathura PDF viewer
 This plugin adds comprehensive text-to-speech functionality to the Zathura
 PDF viewer, enabling users to listen to PDF documents with high-quality
 synthetic speech.
 .
 Features include:
  * Multiple TTS engine support (Piper-TTS, Speech Dispatcher, espeak-ng)
  * Advanced text extraction and processing
  * Keyboard shortcuts for playback control
  * Visual feedback with text highlighting
  * Configurable speech settings (speed, volume, voice)
  * Special content handling (math formulas, tables, links)
  * Session persistence and reading position memory
 .
 The plugin automatically detects and uses the best available TTS engine,
 with graceful fallback to ensure functionality across different systems.

Package: zathura-tts-dev
Architecture: any
Section: libdevel
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
         zathura-tts (= ${binary:Version}),
         libzathura-dev,
         libgirara-dev,
         libglib2.0-dev
Description: Development files for Zathura TTS plugin
 This package contains the development files needed to build extensions
 or applications that integrate with the Zathura TTS plugin.
 .
 It includes header files, API documentation, and example code for
 developers who want to extend the plugin or create custom TTS engines.